0Ottawa%20that%20interfered%20in%20the%20internal%20affairs%20of%20the%20South%20Asian%20nation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Fcanadas-probe-panel-to-examine-indias-alleged-role-in-the-last-two-federal-elections%5C%22%3EOver%20two%20weeks%20ago%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Canada%E2%80%99s%20Public%20Inquiry%20into%20Foreign%20Interference%20in%20Federal%20Electoral%20Processes%20and%20Democratic%20Institutions%20announced%20that%20it%20has%20requested%20the%20Canadian%20government%20to%20provide%20information%20%E2%80%9Crelating%20to%20alleged%20interference%20by%20India%20related%20to%20the%202019%20and%202021%20elections%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUpon%20its%20launch%20in%20September%202023%2C%20the%20Commission%20explicitly%20stated%20its%20intention%20to%20investigate%20interference%20by%20China%2C%20Russia%2C%20and%20unspecified%20%E2%80%9Cforeign%20actors%E2%80%9D%20in%20the%20initial%20phase%20of%20inquiries.%20In%20the%20recent%20press%20release%2C%20expanded%20its%20investigation%20to%20include%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20Thursday%2C%20India%E2%80%99s%20Ministry%20of%20External%20Affairs%20expressed%20outrage%20over%20the%20inclusion%20of%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWe%20have%20seen%20media%20reports%20about%20the%20Canadian%20Commission%20enquiring%20into%20foreign%20interference.%20We%20strongly%20reject%20such%20baseless%20allegations%20of%20Indian%20interference%20in%20Canadian%20elections.%20It%20is%20not%20Government%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20policy%20to%20interfere%20in%20democratic%20processes%20of%20other%20countries%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20MEA%20spokesperson%20Randhir%20Jaiswal%20at%20the%20weekly%20media%20briefing.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFurthermore%2C%20he%20countered%20by%20accusing%20Ottawa%20of%20meddling%20in%20India%E2%80%99s%20domestic%20politics.%20%E2%80%9CIn%20fact%2C%20it%20is%20Canada%20which%20has%20been%20interfering%20in%20our%20internal%20affairs.%20We%20have%20been%20raising%20this%20issue%20regularly%20with%20them.%20We%20continue%20to%20call%20on%20Canada%20to%20take%20effective%20measures%20to%20address%20our%20core%20concerns%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20Canadian%20outlet%20had%20last%20week%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fglobalnews.ca%2Fnews%2F10264872%2Fcanada-china-foreign-interference-elections-csis-report%2F%5C%22%3Epublished%20a%20declassified%20intelligence%20briefing%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20February%202023%20which%20said%20that%20China%20and%20India%20had%20both%20interfered%20in%20last%20two%20general%20elections.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20September%202023%2C%20Canadian%20Prime%20Minister%20Justin%20Trudeau%20alleged%20India%E2%80%99s%20involvement%20in%20the%20shooting%20of%20a%20Canadian%20citizen%2C%20Harpreet%20Singh%20Nijjar%2C%20who%20had%20been%20designated%20as%20a%20Khalistani%20terrorist%20by%20Indian%20security%20agencies.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndia%20vehemently%20refuted%20the%20accusation%2C%20resulting%20in%20the%20expulsion%20of%20one%20diplomat%20from%20each%20nation.%20Additionally%2C%20India%20suspended%20visa%20services%20for%20Canadian%20nationals%2C%20which%20were%20later%20resumed%20after%20approximately%20one%20month.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20response%20to%20India%E2%80%99s%20demand%20for%20diplomatic%20parity%2C%20Ottawa%20had%20to%20recall%20over%2040%20diplomats.%20India%20had%20then%20claimed%20that%20Canadian%20diplomats%20were%20interfering%20in%20Indian%20politics%20but%20had%20not%20shared%20any%20public%20proof.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20Indian%20officials%20had%20repeatedly%20pointed%20to%20statements%20made%20by%20Prime%20Minister%20Trudeau%20during%20the%20farmers%20protest%20in%20India%20as%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fdiplomacy%2Ftrudeau-canada-farmer-protest-internal-affair%5C%22%3Ecompelling%20evidence%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20Canadian%20interference.%20Moreover%2C%20India%20has%20expressed%20frustration%20with%20Canada%E2%80%99s%20perceived%20lack%20of%20action%20in%20curbing%20the%20activities%20of%20pro-Khalistani%20groups%20within%20its%20borders.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Canadian%20Commission%20is%20scheduled%20to%20issue%20an%20interim%20report%20by%20May%203%2C%20followed%20by%20the%20delivery%20of%20its%20final%20report%20by%20the%20year%E2%80%99s%20end.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1707411632000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F21173817%2F1024px-The_Prime_Minister_Shri_Narendra_Modi_with_the_Prime_Minister_of_Canada_Mr._Justin_Trudeau_at_Hyderabad_House_in_New_Delhi_on_February_23_2018_1.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Findia-rejects-allegations-of-election-interference-points-finger-at-ottawa%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Canada%20initiated%20a%20formal%20enquiry%20of%20India's%20alleged%20role%20in%20interfering%20with%20the%20country's%20elections.%20In%20response%2C%20New%20Delhi%20vehemently%20refuted%20the%20accusations%2C%20saying%20that%20it%20was%20actually%20Ottawa%20that%20had%20interfered%20in%20India's%20internal%20affairs.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Findia-rejects-allegations-of-election-interference-points-finger-at-ottawa%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Surya%20Roshni%20Q3%20results%3A%20Net%20profit%20at%20Rs%2090%20crore%3B%20revenue%20falls%204%25%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1707411123000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fbsmedia.business-standard.com%2F_media%2Fbs%2Fimg%2Farticle%2F2016-01%2F11%2Ffull%2F1452458588-3483.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Fcompanies%2Fnews%2Fsurya-roshni-q3-results-net-profit-at-rs-90-crore-revenue-falls-4-124020801736_1.html%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22It%20had%20posted%20a%20consolidated%20net%20profit%20of%20Rs%2089.66%20crore%20in%20the%20October-December%20period%20a%20year%20ago%2C%20according%2