prisoner-hostage%20exchange%2C%20an%20Egyptian%20official%20said.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Fmiddle-east%2Fisrael-pm-orders-troops-to-ready-for-push-into-crowded-rafah%2Farticleshow%2F107532108.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fm-timesofindia-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fm.timesofindia.com%2Fworld%2Fmiddle-east%2Fisrael-pm-orders-troops-to-ready-for-push-into-crowded-rafah%2Famp_articleshow%2F107532108.cms%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fm.timesofindia.com%2Fworld%2Fmiddle-east%2Fisrael-pm-orders-troops-to-ready-for-push-into-crowded-rafah%2Famp_articleshow%2F107532108.cms%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Can%20The%20State%20Discriminate%20Among%20Castes%20Within%20SCs%20and%20STs%3F%20Supreme%20Court%20Reserves%20Judgment%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F31224356%2FSupreme-Court-II-png.png%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20The%20Supreme%20Court%E2%80%99s%20seven-judge%20Constitution%20Bench%20on%20February%208%20(Thursday)%20concluded%20its%20three-day%20hearing%20on%20sub-classification%20of%20Scheduled%20Castes%20and%20Scheduled%20Tribes%20to%20give%20reservations%20for%20more%20backward%20classes.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20%3Ci%3EState%20of%20Punjab%20v%20Davinder%20Singh%2C%20%3C%2Fi%3Ethe%20issue%20before%20the%20top%20court%20bench%20was%20whether%20the%20Punjab%20Scheduled%20Caste%20and%20Backward%20Classes%20(Reservation%20in%20Services)%20Act%2C%202006%2C%20which%20provided%20Balmikis%20and%20Mazhabi%20Sikhs%20with%20%E2%80%9Cfirst%20preference%E2%80%9D%20reservation%20over%2050%25%20of%20the%20total%20seats%20reserved%20for%20the%20SC%20category%2C%20is%20valid.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThose%20who%20favoured%20sub-classification%20within%20the%20SCs%20and%20STs%20to%20ensure%20adequate%20representation%20in%20services%20of%20the%20really%20backward%20among%20them%20relied%20on%20a%20textualist%20interpretation%20of%20the%20constitution%2C%20while%20those%20arguing%20against%20it%20doubted%20whether%20the%20states%20had%20the%20power%20to%20do%20so.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20bench%20comprised%20Chief%20Justice%20of%20India%20(CJI)%20D.Y.%20Chandrachud%2C%20and%20Justices%20B.R.%20Gavai%2C%20Vikram%20Nath%2C%20Bela%20M.%20Trivedi%2C%20Pankaj%20Mithal%2C%20Manoj%20Misra%2C%20and%20Satish%20Chandra%20Sharma.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20CJI%20had%20to%20constitute%20a%20seven-judge%20bench%2C%20in%20view%20of%20the%20fact%20that%20a%20five-judge%20bench%20in%202020%20had%20doubted%20the%20correctness%20of%20the%20decision%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findiankanoon.org%2Fdoc%2F173834%2F%5C%22%3E%3Ci%3EE.V.%20Chinnaiah%20v%20State%20of%20Andhra%20Pradesh%20%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fa%3E(2004)%2C%20where%20another%20five-judge%20bench%20had%20set%20aside%20a%20similar%20law%20in%20Andhra%20Pradesh%20which%20created%20sub-classifications%20within%20the%20SC%20category.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAfter%20the%20%3Cem%3EChinnaiah%3C%2Fem%3E%20ruling%2C%20Andhra%20Pradesh%20did%20not%20enact%20a%20fresh%20law%20and%20instead%20adopted%20a%20%E2%80%98wait%20and%20watch%E2%80%99%20policy%2C%20considering%20the%20Punjab%20government%E2%80%99s%20appeal%20in%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20against%20the%20Punjab%20and%20Haryana%20High%20Court%E2%80%99s%20decision%20to%20strike%20down%20its%202006%20Act%20in%20light%20of%20%3Cem%3EChinnaiah%3C%2Fem%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Punjab%20government%20argued%20before%20the%20apex%20court%2C%20saying%20that%20%3Cem%3EChinnaiah%3C%2Fem%3E%20wrongly%20interpreted%20SCs%20as%20a%20homogenous%20class.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Union%20government%2C%20through%20the%20Attorney%20General%20for%20India%20R.%20Venkataramani%20and%20Solicitor%20General%20Tushar%20Mehta%2C%20also%20supported%20the%20Punjab%20government%E2%80%99s%20stand%2C%20questioning%20the%20validity%20of%20the%20%3Cem%3EChinnaiah%3C%2Fem%3E%20judgment.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20respondents%2C%20however%2C%20had%20argued%20that%20sub-classification%20would%20be%20tantamount%20to%20tinkering%20within%20the%20SC%2FST%20list%2C%20while%20the%20power%20to%20do%20so%20is%2C%20under%20Article%20341%2C%20vested%20only%20with%20the%20President.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESenior%20counsel%20Kapil%20Sibal%20submitted%20that%20SCs%20are%20not%20homogenous%2C%20because%20there%20are%20varying%20levels%20of%20educational%2C%20economic%20and%20social%20development%20among%20the%20castes%20grouped%20under%20the%20SCs.%20Secondly%2C%20he%20argued%20that%20the%201950%20presidential%20order%2C%20which%20lists%20state-wise%20SCs%2C%20is%20meant%20for%20identification%2C%20and%20not%20for%20extending%20reservation%20benefits.%20Therefore%2C%20he%20said%20that%20in%20%3Cem%3EChinnaiah%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20the%20court%20wrongly%20concluded%20that%20sub-classification%20amounted%20to%20tinkering%20with%20the%20presidential%20list.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESibal%20was%20representing%20Mazhabi%20Sikhs%20and%20Balmiki%2012.5%25%20Rakhvankaran%20Bachao%20Morcha.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAdvocate%20Gopal%20Sankaranarayanan%2C%20representing%20Madiga%20Jana%20Seva%20Samithi%2C%20an%20intervening%20party%2C%20questioned%20the%20practice%20of%20extending%20reservation%20benefits%20to%20castes%20within%20the%20SCs%20that%20are%20already%20adequately%20represented%2C%20because%20the%20State%20is%20helpless%20in%20identifying%20the%20most%20backward%20among%20them%20deserving%20more%20reservation%20within%20the%20quota.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESub-classification%2C%20he%20felt%2C%20eventually%20would%20pave%20the%20way%20for%20doing%20away%20with%20the%20reservation%20altogether%2C%20because%20those%20castes%20which%20are%20forward%20enough%20could%20be%20deprived%20of%20excessive%20reservation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESenior%20counsel%20K.K.%20Venugopal%2C%20arguing%20for%20Madiga%20Reservation%20Porata%20Samiti%2C%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CWhen%20there%20is%20no%20sub-categorisation%2C%20the%20weakest%20of%20the%20weak%20will%20fall%20to%20the%20ground%20and%20the%20stronger%20ones%20therein%20will%20end%20up%20getting%20the%20lion%E2%80%99s%20share%2C%20thereby%20negating%20the%20entire%20reason%20why%20the%20reservation%20was%20there%20in%20the%20first%20place.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20submitted%20that%20the%20State%20was%20bound%20to%20sub-classify%20in%20view%20of%20the%20constitutional%20mandate%20under%20Article%2038(2)%2C%20to%20eliminate%20inequalities%20in%20income%20and%20status%20amongst%20groups%20of%20people.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fprsindia.org%2Ffiles%2Fbills_acts%2Facts_states%2Ftamil-nadu%2F2009%2F2009TN4.pdf%5C%22%3ETamil%20Nadu%20Arunthathiyars%20Act%2C%202009%2C%3C%2Fa%3E%20which%20allocated%20a%20certain%20number%20of%20seats%20in%20educational%20institutions%20and%20government%20services%20to%20the%20Arunthathiyar%20community%20within%20the%20SCs%20in%20the%20State%2C%20is%20also%20under%20challenge%20before%20the%20Supreme%20Court.%20Its%20counsel%20Shekhar%20Naphade%20submitted%20that%20if%20sub-classification%20is%20supported%20by%20empirical%20data%2C%20then%20it%20should%20be%20valid.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EArguments%20against%20sub-classification%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20respondents%2C%20who%20submitted%20that%20%3Ci%3EChinnaiah%3C%2Fi%3E%20was%20correctly%20decided%20by%20the%20court%2C%20relied%20on%20the%20homogenous%20character%20of%20SCs%2C%20which%20shared%20the%20common%20stigma%20of%20%E2%80%98untouchability%E2%80%99.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESenior%20counsel%20Sanjay%20Hegde%2C%20for%20instance%2C%20argued%20that%20constitution-makers%20did%20not%20go%20into%20the%20question%20of%20the%20degree%20of%20suffering%20of%20%E2%80%98untouchability%E2%80%99%20by%20these%20castes%2C%20to%20determine%20their%20inclusion%20in%20the%20SC%20category%2C%20and%20therefore%2C%20it%20is%20not%20permissible%20to%20bring%20in%20fresh%20criteria%20to%20differentiate%20among%20them%20to%20determine%20who%20among%20them%20deserve%20greater%20reservation%20benefits.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHegde%20also%20argued%20against%20sub-classification%20of%20SCs%20on%20the%20apprehension%20that%20it%20could%20lead%20to%20balkanisation%20and%20pitting%20one%20SC%20against%20another%20after%20the%20violence%20witnessed%20in%20Manipur%20recently%2C%20which%20occurred%20after%20the%20high%20court%E2%80%99s%20directive%20to%20the%20state%20government%20to%20include%20the%20Meitei%20community%20in%20the%20ST%20list.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20pitted%20the%20Meiteis%20against%20the%20Kukis%2C%20who%20were%20already%20in%20the%20ST%20list%2C%20and%20who%20feared%20that%20Meiteis%20would%20be%20able%20to%20purchase%20land%20in%20the%20prohibited%20hilly%20areas%2C%20if%20included%20in%20the%20ST%20list.%20Inclusion%20and%20exclusion%20of%20castes%20from%20the%20SC%20and%20ST%20list%20should%20be%20done%20only%20by%20Parliament%2C%20and%20not%20by%20the%20state%20governments%2C%20he%20submitted.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOthers%20among%20the%20respondents%20said%20that%20if%20sub-classification%20is%20permitted%2C%20it%20could%20lead%20to%20discrimination%20against%20certain%20castes%20within%20the%20SCs%20and%20STs%2C%20depriving%20their%20entitlement%20to%20the%20entire%20reservation%20quota%20meant%20for%20SCs%20and%20STs.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20response%2C%20the%20Punjab%20government%20submitted%20that%20both%20Articles%2015(4)%20and%2016(4)%20permitted%20greater%20discretion%20on%20behalf%20of%20the%20Union%20and%20state%20governments%20to%20identify%20backward%20classes%20among%20the%20SCs%20and%20STs.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Punjab%20government%20submitted%20that%20the%20language%20of%20Article%2015(4)%20suggests%20that%20the%20State%20can%20make%20any%20special%20provision%20for%20the%20%E2%80%9Cadvancement%E2%80%9D%20of%20any%20caste%20among%20the%20SCs%20and%20STs.%20However%2C%20CJI%20Chandrachud%20disagreed%20and%20told%20its%20Advocate%20General%2C%20Gurminder%20Singh%2C%20that%20the%20word%20%E2%80%9Cadvancement%20of%20any%20%E2%80%9D%20used%20in%20this%20article%20pertained%20only%20to%20SEBCs%20%5Bsocially%20and%20educationally%20backward%20classes%5D%20and%20not%20for%20SCs%20and%20STs%2C%20as%20the%20latter%20has%20been%20conceived%20in%20a%20homogenous%20manner.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20the%20CJI%20agreed%20with%20Singh%20regarding%20his%20interpretation%20of%20the%20language%20adopted%20in%20Article%2016(4)%2C%20which%20states%20that%20nothing%20in%20this%20article%20shall%20prevent%20the%20State%20from%20making%20any%20provision%20for%20the%20reservation%20of%20appointments%20or%20posts%20in%20favour%20of%20any%20backward%20class%20of%20citizens%20which%2C%20in%20the%20opinion%20of%20the%20State%2C%20is%20not%20adequately%20represented%20in%20the%20services%20under%20the%20State.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20the%20SCs%20and%20STs%20are%20included%20within%20the%20%E2%80%9Cbackward%20class%20of%20citizens%E2%80%9D%20in%20this%20Article%2C%20Singh%20contended%20that%20it%20conferred%20maximum%20discretion%20on%20the%20governments%20to%20identify%20those%20castes%20within%20the%20SC%2FST%20fold%20who%20are%20not%20adequately%20represented%2C%20and%20confer%20greater%20reservation%20on%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1707404360000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F31224356%2FSupreme-Court-II-png.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fclass-within-class-can-the-state-discriminate-among-castes-within-scs-and-sts-sc-reserves-judgment%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Those%20who%20favoured%20sub-classification%20within%20the%20SCs%20and%20STs%20to%20ensure%20adequate%20representation%20in%20services%20of%20the%20really%20backward%20among%20them%20relied%20on%20a%20textualist%20interpretation%20of%20the%20constitution%2C%20while%20those%20arguing%20against%20it%20doubted%20whether%20the%20states%20had%20the%20