%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%E2%80%98My%20judges%E2%80%99%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETrump%E2%80%99s%20relationship%20with%20the%20federal%20judiciary%20%E2%80%93%20both%20the%20judges%20who%20serve%20in%20the%20federal%20judiciary%20and%20the%20broader%20legal%20institution%20itself%20%E2%80%93%20differs%20from%20that%20of%20his%20predecessors.%20He%20talks%20about%20the%20court%20system%20not%20as%20an%20independent%20branch%20of%20government%20but%20as%20a%20political%20institution%20whose%20positions%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftime.com%2F4266700%2Fdonald-trump-supreme-court-nominations%2F%5C%22%3Eshould%20align%3C%2Fa%3E%20with%20his%20own.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20his%20Jan.%206%2C%202021%2C%20speech%20before%20the%20attack%20on%20the%20U.S.%20Capitol%2C%20Trump%20sounded%20miffed%20at%20the%20three%20justices%20he%20had%20nominated%20to%20the%20Supreme%20Court.%20They%20were%20ruling%20against%20him%20now%2C%20he%20said%2C%20perhaps%20to%20counter%20the%20perception%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2023%2F12%2F21%2Fus%2Fpolitics%2Ftrump-supreme-court.html%5C%22%3E%E2%80%9Cthey%E2%80%99re%20my%20puppets.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EModern%20presidents%20have%20always%20sought%20to%20mould%20the%20judiciary%20by%20selecting%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.upress.virginia.edu%2Ftitle%2F3596%2F%5C%22%3Ejustices%20whose%20records%3C%2Fa%3E%20align%20with%20the%20nominating%20president%E2%80%99s%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fyalebooks.yale.edu%2Fbook%2F9780300080735%2Fpicking-federal-judges%2F%5C%22%3Epolitical%20preferences%3C%2Fa%3E.%20But%20historically%2C%20presidents%20were%20careful%20to%20discuss%20the%20courts%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cambridge.org%2Fcore%2Fbooks%2Fcurbing-the-court%2F97B607067A2E7392C2223EF7E642FC7A%5C%22%3Elegalistic%20terms%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdoi.org%2F10.1111%2F1468-2508.00207%5C%22%3Eavoid%20politicizing%20the%